text: Bottle at Højbjerg tasting. Pours hazy pale gold with a frothy white head. Aroma of hops, fruit, and floral notes. Light sweetness, medium bitterness. Light to medium body, slight watery texture, average carbonation.

Bottle @ Johns. Pours yellow with a white head. Aroma of malt, little yeast, light spice, citrus, lemonpeel. Flavor is light sweet, light bitter, malt, fruit, citrus. Medium body, average to lively carbonation, light bitter finish. 7-3-7-3-15. 170617
Bottle. Creamy white good mostly lasting head. Yellow colour. Moderate malty and light hoppy aroma. Light bitter flavor. Average light bitter finish. Oily palate.
Bottle @ Højbjerg tasting. Nice head with good duration. Color is golden. Aroma and taste are rich hops, fruits, flowers and malt. Nice bitter finish.

Bottle, 6%. Slightly hazy dark yellow with small white head. Aroma is malt, fruit, hop, citrus and fruit peel. Flavour is malt, fruit, hop, citrus, fruit peel, medium sweet, orange, herbs, little honey and medium bitter.

Golden, medium hazy with bog, frothy, semi-thick, white head. Aroma is grainy, pale, fruity, peachy. Taste is moderate bitter - long and stable. Medium body, creamy and oily texture, average carbonation, finish is moderately bitter, biscuit, lemon. In overall mild, not very interesting, some fruity/peachy accents, quite bitter as for a cream ale.
Gyllengul till orange öl med ett större vitt skum. Doft och smak av citrus och gräs. Även en lättare maltighet och säd.

hazy pale yellow colour, medium sized dense, though not too stable white head; aroma and taste of grape seed and skins, some tropical fruitiness and lemony, as well as biscuity notes; correct beer, though nothing extraordinary
Light opaque yellow, white lacing foam head. Crisp aroma, fresh taste. Pleasant beer. (Velp 201611)
backlog. yellow with a white head. Aroma has slight citrus, bread. Fruity and somewhat hoppy. Decent

Coz to kremowe ale faktycznie ma fajna kremowa pianke i bardzo jaskrawa zolta barwe o mglistym zabarwieniu, pachnie swiezoscia lata, rumiankiem. W smaku platki owsiane, troche papaji i kandyzowanego ananasa. Delikatne, lekko gozkie. Smaczne. Doskonala alternatywa dla lagera latem.

33cl Bottle at home.
Appearance: Hazy yellow colour with medium white head, with a ok retention.
 Aroma: fruity, lemon, zesty citrus, hops, grassy, tropical fruits, mild pine, peaches.
Taste: moderate bitter, moderate sweet, Quitey Fruisty with zesty citrus, grass, pine, tropical fruit peach with a dyr hoppy Bitter finish..
 Body is medium,carbonation is average.

Złote, zmętnione. Piana biała, drobna. Jest bardzo trwała. 
Aromat mocno chmielowy, mnóstwo cytrusów, ale pod nimi nuta żółtych owoców. 
Jest trochę nut pszenicznych w aromacie. 
Całość pachnie mocno chmielowo, ale "gładko"
W smaku średnia goryczka. Na początku cytrusowa, potem bardziej nuty albedo, głównie w posmaku. 
Mimo to jest bardzo gładkie w odczuciu. Rzeczywiście gdyby nie spora ilość chmielu było by niemalże kremowe. 
Bardzo dobre piwo.
Bottle Hazy yellow colour with medium white head.Aroma of yeast and citrus feel slight bitter and malty with good fruity mouthfeels and hoppy dry finish.
Bottle. Light straw color, good white foam. Aroma: citrus, fruits, yeast, even a bit of menthol. Taste: sweet, fruit, citrus, candy, mild hop bitterness.
Bottle. It pours hazy yellow with lots of floaties and a big thick white head. The aroma is fruity hoppy with light malty notes. Pineapple and oranges in the flavor. Some citrus and creamy malts.

Bottle shared at a tasting at troubless place. Hazy yellow with white head. Very hoppy aroma with notes of tropical fruits, herbs and citrus. Very bitter flavor, hoppy with notes of citrus, some tropical fruits, lager-ish, dry. Light to medium-bodied.

Bottle shared at a tasting. Cloudy yellow. Aroma is of hops with notes of tropical fruits (mango, passion fruit). Sweetish, fruity, flavors of guava, citrus, nice bitterness. Medium-bodied, oily palate, easy drinking. Nice.

Bottle sample at a tasting at troubless place. Thanks zvsn & rayaron. Cloudy yellow. Nice fruity hops aroma, passion fruit. Dry flavor with moderately bitter fruity hops. Quite light-bodied. Nice and refreshing.

bleek geel/gouden met volle fijne witte kraag, aroma van gras, kruidig. smaken zijn matig bitter, matig zoet, zachte co2, grassig/kruidig karakter, smooth, droog mondgevoel, fruitig, prima maar matige body.

Hazy pale yellow color, average sized white head. Aroma of citrus, grapefruit, some spiciness, malt. Taste is similar and pretty straightforward, grapefruit juice, lime, lemongrass, solid malty backbone. Light to medium body, soft to average carbonation. Very tasty and very clean.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Bottle 0,33l. Cloudy pale yellow liquid with average white head. Intensive aroma. Smell of pine, tropical fruirts, flowers. Light body, medium carbonation. Taste of dried grass and flowers, some tropical fruits, a hint of sourness and sweetness.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

(To Øl Primals Cream) Bottle 330 ml at home, served into a shaker, ABV 6%
Bright yellow colour on the body, clear, with lots of activity in the glass and a finger of white, thick head on top, with very good retention.
Aroma has lots of tropical fruits, melon, pineapple.
Taste is mildly sweet with a nice bitter finish. Again melon, tropical fruits, grass, peach.
Medium body, soft carbonation, nicely dry on the palate.
Very good.

На кране в 1516 СПб. 
Золотис цвет, с небольш& шапкой. Очень хмелево& персико& аромат с нотками овсяных хлопьев. мягкий, немного кремовы& вкус с легкой горчинк& и долгим послевк& Отлично& пиво.
Bottle at home. Aroma is quite fruity, lemon, zesty citrus, hops, grassy, tropical fruits, mild pine, peach. Flavour is moderate to medium bitter. Body is medium. Lovely crisp fruit bomb!

Flaska (tack NordicV). Dimmigt gul med ett frostigt vitt skum. Dofter av citron, persika, vått gräs och skog. Smakinslag av citron, blomster, apelsin och gräs. Medelbeska, sur och fruktig avslutning, torr munkänsla. Mycket bra.

Bottle, bought @ Kihoskh, Cph.
Pours clear golden with a large, staying, creamy White head. Aroma is very grassy, light grapefruit, some zesty oranges. Still some clean maltiness. Medium carbonation, fine dry and quite creamy mouthfeel. Flavour is elegant, crisp malts, light hay, serious bitterness, grassy, hops oil, floral. Lidt orange peel. Lingering light chalky bitterness. Nice and fresh.

330 ml. bottle shared with Kraddel. Text on the back reads Its a real primal thing, watching someone get hurt. Its fun and accessible. o.O Pours very hazy golden with a creamy white head. Nose is lots of lemon grass, freshly cut green grass hops that briefly reminds me of Taras Boulba, faint sugar, corn bread base. Taste is great mix of green grass hops, floral, lemon grass, green hops & sweetish grain base, white bread & faint vanilla. Drinks really easily, mildly creamy. Really nice beer.
Thnx to Ships. Pours unclear blonde. Small white head. Smell is malty, rye-like aspects. Taste is Sharp, bit bitter, Nice body and carbo. Easy drinkable. Good !
Bottle, 330 ml from Pivoljub. Shared with Miro. Pours clear golden huge white head. Bit perfumy, grapefruit, citrus, flowery. Sweet, bitterish finish. Very drinkable, quite refreshing.

Aromat średnio intensywny, słodowy, trawiasty, cytrusowy, trochę przyprawowy. Barwa złota, opalizujące. Piana biała, średnio obfita, trwała, ładny lacing. W smaku raczej wytrawne, owocowe, cytrusy, grejpfrut, lekka kwiatowość. Średnia goryczka, niskie wysycenie. Bardzo fajne, bardzo orzeźwiające.

0.33 l bottle from drankgigant.nl, best before June 2017. Minimally hazy, straw yellow with a medium large, frothy, stable, white head. Fruity-grassy aroma of grapefruit, lemon, pineapple and fresh cut grass. Sweetish, fruity-grassy taste of grapefruit, pineapple, lemon and fresh cut grass, followed by a short, moderately bitter-grassy finish. Medium body, smooth and slightly effervescent mouthfeel, average carbonation. Very refreshing, easily drinkable and round. Very nice stuff!

33 cl bottle from Kihoskh. Hazy, golden colour with a thin, white head. Fruity aroma with citrus fruits, grasses, an underlying fruitiness. Taste is bitter. Medium body with a creamy texture and a lively carbonation. Finishes rather dry and bitter with citrus fruits and grape. Excellent, dry Cream Ale.
Bottle from Kihoskh. Hazy yellow with a white head. Aroma is sweet, malty and moderate hoppy - citrus and peach. Flavor is quite sweet and moderate bitter. Dry and moderate bitter finish. 010316

Bottle (from beergium). Pours hazy golden with whiteish head. The aroma is sweet, fruits, citrus lychee, mango. Flavor is sweet and bitter, citrus, lemon, grapefruit, mango, some diesel. Finish is grapefruit bitter. Body is bit thin, alcohol is well covered. Overall: good.

Bottle. Nose is an abundance of citrus, tangerine, lemon, orange, pithy, hints of lime. Taste is very light, not the hop bomb the nose implied; light cereal, malt and a dry herbal hop finish with grapefruit characteristics and the bitter note people define as cat piss. Its very drinkable, and the mouthfeel is surprisingly full. 

Cream ale is not a style I really know, but I found this enjoyable.

Cremiger, hefig hopfiger Beginn mit deutlicher Grasigkeit. Die Hopfigkeit bleibt konstant während die Herbe deutlich steigt, geringe Bitterkeit, süffig. Langer hopfiger Nachhal, zunehmend trocken. Gut. 11/10/11/11/10/11
Bottle from Kihoskh, Copenhagen - golden pour with white head. Citric fruity and floral hoppy aroma and taste, some nice satsuma and lemon notes, light peachy, pleasant number.

33cl bottle. Pale yellow, clear, with a saison-style white head. Smells like lemon zest, flowers, honey and a bit of farmhouse funkiness. Bitter, crisp and refreshing, with notes of lemon, bitter grapefruit and salt.

330 ml bottle. Hazy golden colour with white head which stays for a long time. Aroma of citrus fruits,dry. Taste of grapefruits,grape, orange. Light bitterness. Not my cup of tea but good drinkable beer
Pale yellow colour. Light citrusy hop in the aroma together with a mild skunkiness. Fresh and fruity hoppy flavour with a touch of pale malt in the finish.

Bottle. Grapefruit complemented by floral and pine notes. A spiciness that culminates in notes of cat piss, but curiously enough, the latter dont spoil the drinking axperience in any degree. Pale malty body and a creamy mouthfeel. Excellent.
330ml bottle from HK Brewcraft. Pours hazy light yellow. Very pleasant aroma. Light, floral taste. Slightly bitter finish

Aroma: perfume, zest, spices, lavender.
Taste: dry with light bitternesss.

Strange and over perfumed.

Bottle from Rehills, Newcastle. Hazy straw coloured with a white head of foam. It has a sweet tropical fruit and slight tart lemon flavour followed by a spicy, warming, creamy and slight earthy finish. Very Good.
330ml bottle. Pours hazy gold with large white head. High carbonation with a fruity citrus aroma. Quite crisp, zesty and light. Some floral, peppery notes. Good.
Trübes gelb mit durchschnittlicher Schaumkrone. Fruchtig, Zitrus, Orange, Melone, leicht, süffig, dezent bitter.
bottle at home from aleselainteresting citra like mango notes on a fairly soft and light body, moderate carbonation, 0 perceptible bitterness, a little slick in mouth. Interesting take.

Bottle at home. Slightly hazy light golden with big white head. Yoghurt, cucumber, spicess, spring onion. Grassy freshness, doughy yeast taste. Hop bitterness has the overhand in an otherwise creamy and mild spicy palate. Finish is earthy bitter.

L:
-pours a hazy straw golden with a big,foamy,white head
-low to medium carbonation visible
S:
-pineapple,lemon,zesty,grassy,herbal, the nose except the mustard
-high bitterniss for the style
F:
-medium carbonation
-light body
O:
More of a Pale Ale to me.
Good overall

Bottle shared. Pours very hazy golden with a white head. Aroma of citrus, grassy hops, light fruits and floral notes. Flavour is above light sweet and over moderate bitter. Above light bodied with light carbonation.

33cl bottle courtesy of and shared with Kermis.
Thick creamy white head. Cloudy blond pour. Nice bitterness. easy drinking

Pours a slightly hazy straw golden color, topped with a medium frothy head, white and fairly lasting. Strong citrusy aroma, you can notice it from far, quite lemony. Taste is citrusy and decently bitter, slight herbal hoppy feel in the finish. Nice and light, full taste. A bit peppery in the finish and aftertaste. Very lovely.

from a 330ml bottle on 30/11/2015. Pours a slightly cloudy straw with a big, fluffy white head. Has a pleasant mild zesty aroma with some citrus and spice. Take a sip and theres lemon at the top, with some wheat notes, followed by a touch of honeyed sweetness, balanced by a delicate sour bitterness. Has a creamy mouthfeel and soft carbonation. I really like this - itd be an absolutely perfect, refreshing, supremely quaffable summer brew. Has a touch of imperial pils about it.
Clear yellow colour with small head. Aroma has lemon, grass and some spices. Taste has also lemon, grass and some grapefruit bitterness. Stingy carbonation and light body. A lot like wit beer.
33cl bottle at home. Somewhat hazy yellow with a small white head. Light to medium body with moderate carbonation. Nice bitterness with subtle fruity tones. Citrus, pine, yeast and tart. Tasty ale.

Déjà, jaime bien le jeu de mot ... Sinon, jolie texture en bouche / assez directe: piquante et amère/acidulée/florale. Belle astringence en fin de bouche ! Plus citronnée et florale en se réchauffant. Vraiment chouette.
On tap at Biercb. GOlden colour with white head. Hoppy, citric aroma. Bitter, hoppy, citric tate. Medium body.

7th October 2015Hazy yellow - gold beer, good white head. Palate is airy with a fine minerally crispness. Light malts with light creamy sweetness. Sweet floralness ensues, then floral grapefruit and pith. Mild pine and orange. Light crisp finish. Mild citric peel bitter linger. Hangs together very well, most quaffable!

Bottle from Bottle Baron. Milky golden body with a lasting white head. Good lacing. Aroma of soured cream, grass, flower petals and passionfruit. Flavour of white sugar, cream and honey. Medium body with a slick texture. Light fizz. Sweet but with an off-putting sour note in the aroma.

Draught. Pours a hazy golden yellow with a mostly fading off white head. Aroma of citrus, bready, grassy, slightly sweet. Taste is of citrus fruits, some grapefruit, slightly woody, some peach. Soft creamy mouthfeel, very nice.
Bottle from cerveteca lisboa, portugal. Hazy gold color. Thin to medium white head. Medium bitterness. Flavour is light waterish, light hop, light grassy. Quite good!

6%ABV. Cream Ale.

Tapped out a cloudy golden yellow, about 5ºSRM.

Nose has beautiful bright citrus flavors. Like sniffing the cap off a botle of lemon fizz or an Orangina. There is a nice hit of clean wheaty flavors.

Mouthfeel is lightly soapy with a pronounced hop-balanced You get some nice bright piney resinous freshness right off. Clean biscuit, white bread like flavors, cleanly cut off by the hops.

Goes on Favorites List!

Bottle, Pours is golden clear with thick white head. Aroma of grain, malts, corn, floral, fruity, some peach, light orange, light pineapple. Taste is moderate bitter, moderate sweet, orange and fruity mouthfeel. Medium body, creamy texture, light, bitter finish. Citrusy fresh, good one!

Hazy, bright yellow color with white head. Aroma is really intense, with lots of citrus fruits and floral notes. Taste is somehow mild but also hoppy. A slight yeasty note at first, herbal and floral hops in the middle and some nice bitterness in the finish. Overall this is a really nice, hoppy cream ale.
Bottle. Pine, tropical fruits, citrus, grains. Creamy texture. Mild bitterness.

Draught @ BrewDog Helsinki, Tarkkampujankatu 20, 00150 Helsinki, Finland. [ As To Øl Primals Cream ].Unclear medium orange color with a average, frothy, good lacing, mostly lasting to diminishing, off-white head. Aroma is moderate malty, caramel, moderate to heavy hoppy, citrus, peach, orange - citrus. Flavor is moderate to light heavy sweet and bitter with a long duration, sweet fruit, peach. Body is medium, texture is oily to watery, carbonation is soft. [20150722]

Bottle @ Mbargo. Hazy light golden, creamy white head, good lacing. Hoppy and juciy aroma, pineapple, citrus. Medium carbonated smooth and dry mouthfeel. Fruity taste, tropical juice, sweet orange, some mild citrus bitterness.

Bottle from Cotteridge Wines; clear straw yellow pour with a frothy white head, aroma has citrus and a hint of cream, taste has citrus and lemon mousse, floral action, not the creamiest of cream ales.

Dourada, alaranjada, levemente turva, espuma irregular de boa formação e retenção, aspecto cremoso. Aroma cítrico de laranja, adocicado, um pouco de baunilha e pêssego, leve fermento e lúpulo, malte ainda mais fraco. Paladar mantém a criticidade e o leve fermento, amargor um pouco mais intenso do que no aroma. Corpo leve, média carbonatação. Aftertaste refrescante, misto de laranja com lúpulo, com o aumento da temperatura o dulçor lembra a mel. Boa !
33 cl bottle @ home. Pours slightly cloudy yellow with a white head that leaves some lacing. Aroma and flavour are citrus, flowers, malt, and pine - with a slightly bitter finish.

Pours straw like haze, with stable yellowish creamy head.
Aroma without note of an alcohol, with strong presence of tropical fruit.
Flavor is mouthfeel sweet like biscuit, with strong bitter fuity notes (papaya, lemon, orange peel etc.).
Finish is dry bitter, body is sticky, carbonation is low.
Hop bitterness is medium to high, malt sweetness is mild medium.

UPDATED: SEP 22, 2015 Bottle from 100 piv. Yellow golden color with huge white head. Yeast, citrus hops in aroma. Nice hoppy bitter taste, Belgian yeast, spices. Solid malty backbone. Long spicy hoppy bitter finish. Tasty.

Bottle at 100 piv. Aroma intense lemony flowery zesty hoppy. Clear golden colour, stable white head. Taste is very nicely balanced, complex combination of subtle hops, flowery, lemony, grapes, spicy. Thin bodied and sessionable. Complex and pleasant and excellent.
33cl bottle. Pours slight hazy golden with a small good lasting white head. Aroma of citrus fruits, lemon, herbs. Taste is dry hoppy, citrus, melon, mild hops.

Draught at Hatten. 
Pours yellow. 
Aroma of orange marmalade and a hint of peanuts. 
Dry hoppy citrus, clean.

Draft at hatten.
Pale hazy, thin white head.
Aroma of nuts, 
Taste sweet bitter grape fruit cereal. Thick feel

Bottle. Pours a clear golden with a fizzy, white head. Aroma is hoppy, grainy, honey, floral, juicy yet dry. Taste is sweet, juicy and very bitter-hoppy. Tropical fruit sweetness, nice and fresh, dry finish. High carbonation and a slightly oily body.

Bottle from Kihoskh. Pours subtle hazy yellow with a medium white head. Aromas of corn, grain, citrus, hops, elderflower, honey-like sweetness. Taste is fresh hops, grain, dry bitter citrus, orange peel.
On tap at Mikkeller & Friends, Copenhagen. Pours hazy golden with small white head. Aroma of tropical fruits, coffee. Taste hippy bitterness with quite some sweetness and a little fruity sourness.
Zu schreien gab es hier eigentlich recht wenig. Etwas zu getreidig, leicht hopfig, dazu ordentlich Brot und eine gewisse Erdigkeit. Ganz ok.

Bottle from Rudat in Dortmund. The beer has got a hazy golden-strawy colour with an airy head and medium to thin body. Aroma of hops, pine, citrus and soap. Taste of bitter hops, flowers, soap, bread, dust, straw. Bitter-light acid finish with a thin touch.

Draft @ Bishops Arms Gustav, Malmö. Pours a hazy yellow color with a small white head. Has a fruity piney hoppy creamy aroma. Fruity malty bitter creamy hoppy flavor. Has a fruity malty hoppy bitter piney creamy finish.
Bottle from Kihoskh. Pale golden pour with a frothy head. Tropical fruits, corn, syrup, grains with a light bitterness.

Fat på Bishop Arms, Gustav i Malmö. Smak och doft av humle, malt, mango, persika, aprikos, citrus, karamell med toner av örter. Lätt kropp och sötma, fruktig och frisk, rund, lätt oljig, beska med smak av citrusskal.

Draught @ Haket. Pours hazy yellow with a small frothy and bubbly white head that leaves some small trace on the glass while dissipating. Smell is slightly malty and slightly herbal with bread, grass, lemon balm, grapefruit rinds and lemon zest. Taste is slightly sweet, slightly bitter, slightly fruity and slightly herbal. Mouthfeel is round, tiny astringent and medium bodied. Finish is bitter with crackers, bread, grapefruit juice, lemon balm, simple syrup, moist grass, pine needles, minerals, orange zest and lemon zest. Bit bready but quite quaffable...

On tap at Bishops Arms Gustav Adolfs Torg, Malmö. 

Golden with a white head. Aroma and taste of grass, fruit, caramel, bread and some citrus. Medium bitterness and body.
@ Bishops GA Malmö 15-8-6: Stor trevlig doft av frukt, vete och kryddor. Smaken är ganska potent med stora söta toner. Komplex smak.

How: Draught.
Where: BrewDog Kungsholmen, Stockholm.
Appearance: Pale golden colour with a white head.
Aroma: Hops, fruit, sour milk, some caramel.
Body: Medium body and carbonation.
Flavour: Malt, fruit, bread, citrus, some bitterness.

Tap @ Konttori.
Pours golden color with a thick white head. Somewhat herbal and grassy aroma, orange with mild hops and even some spruce. Fruity flavor, sweet toffee notes, creamy palate with a lingering bitter finish. Balanced and surprisingly refreshing for a Cream Ale.
3415
Bottle. Golden color, white head. Aroma of citrus, peach and creamy wheat. Taste is soft and fruity, with citrus, peach, pine and caramelly bread. Good hoppy cream ale.

Orangeish golden colour, not much head. Aroma is fruity, floral, some earthy and mild bready notes to it. Flavour is fruity, floral, bready and mildly toffeeish with a bit grainy notes to it as well.
On tap at the Rover. Cloudy yellow with white head. Aroma heavy yeasty, lots of Mango and peach. Taste is similar, lots of fruit, Mango, peach, apricot, and yeast

Bottle 330ml @ Rekord Bar, Drammen
Pours hazy golden with a white head. Aroma has notes of malt, caramel, floral and citrus, Taste is medium sweet and light to medium bitter with a long medium, texture is thin to oily, carbonation is soft.

Draught at BBB
Slightly hazy pale golden with a white, creamy head. 
Floral hops in the aroma. 
Creamy mouthfeel with a medium to high bitterness. 
Citrus and wet hay in the flavour.

Draught. Almost clear golden liquid with small white head. Aroma of grain, citrus, light sulphur, butter and floral hops. Taste is light sweet and light bitter with notes of citrus, light sulphur and grain. Light to medium bodied with medium carbonation. Decent.

Draught at Brewers Beer Bar, Göteborg. Clear pale golden beer with a nice and lasting offwhite head. Hoppy fruity flavor, grassy, pine apples, mango, biscuit notes. Hoppy pine and mango flavor, peach, biscuits, hay, some woody notes. Maybe not totally true to the style, but pretty damn good.
Nice golden colour, white stable head. Fruity, lemony, grassy taste. Bit malty, easy drinkable. Fair bittereness in the end. Enjoy it in the sun!

Appearance: Clear pale golden color with a fine white head. Ok lacing.Aroma: Fresh citrus and malty.Palate: Medium body. Fine balance between sweetness and bitterness. Average carbonation. Semi dry texture.Taste: Citrus, malty and some yeast.Overall impression: Fresh summer ale.Personal stats: Bottle at Brygghus 9 in Trondheim, Norway

Bottle shared with KL at Søstrene Karlsen bar & kjøkken, Trondheim. Slightly hazy golden. White head. Not much lacing. Aroma of freah tropical fruits, citrus, marmelade, succade and a fashionable hint of feline urine. Similar, and very fine taste. Moderate bitterness. Very quaffable!
Noe tåkete lys brun med høyt hvitt kremete skum. Lukter fruktig, ananas, fersken. Smaker søtt, fruktig sydhavsfrukt i starten før medium bitterhet overtar. Medium lang bitter avslutning. noe tørr
A small taste from a friend @ One Pint Pub. Pours hazy amber with a medium head. Aroma is creamy fruity malts. Flavor is creamy malts with fruits and hops. Very nice.

0,33 bottle at Boban place in Vranovo-Serbia, courtesy of Johnny Off L. guys. Pours hazy golden with a creamy white head which lowers leaving drafts. Nose: mild dry hopping, grainy malty notes. Mouth: low or no bitterness, no watery feel but easy drinking, far away sweet background and dry end. Good. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bottle @ Apollon, Bergen. Birthday rating no. 1, hurray! :-D Pours a slightly hazy light golden body with a large creamy white head. Aroma is grains, straw, red berries, yeast and hints of grape peel and hay. Taste is red berries, grape peel, straw, grains and hints of pale malts, white pepper, hay and yeast. Light to medium body and high, near-fizzy carbonation. Refreshing and assertive within its style, well brewed by To Øl.
Tap at Beer Hunters. Orange-amber color, huge cloudy white head. Aroma has apricot, alcohol and citrus. Medium-bodied. Yup, creamy texture. Citrus, apricot, mango. Fruity. Meh.

Keg at PSBH, Manchester. Hazy golden/orange. White head with lacing. Passionfruit and lemon disinfectant aroma. Taste is gritty citrus, red berry, minerally. Sweet malty linger. Reminds me quite a bit of Sweet Action so they mustve got near the mark.

Draught@Ølhus Kobenhavn, Helsinki. Slightly cloudy golden color, rich white head. Citric hop aroma. Smooth, floral hop flavor with a full, velvety mouthfeel. Medium-light body, medium carbonation. Interesting take on the style!
Bottle oro leggermente velata buon naso luppolato agrumato fruttato tocco esotico lieve resina leggero cereale buona secchezza abbastanza gasata buon amato finale leggermente citrico

Kindly shared by Jaghana. 
Couleur jaune trouble. tès légère mousse. Nez bien houblonné citronné (type Ipa). Gout houblonné pamplemousse bien amer, puis bien malté. Corps moyen. Fin maltée fruitée. Ressemble a une Ipa.

Bottle 33cl, a clear golden beer with medium head. Nose is on dry lemon and grapefruit. Aroma is intense on lemon and grapefruit, body medium to low, medium sweet, high bitterness, good body with pleasant cereals notes. Would be better with less grapefruit there.
Draught at Mikkeller&Friends. Clear yellow - white head. Toasted. Dryness. Bread notes. Light fruity. Ok bitterness. Citrus. Light body. #Terassebasker. Super fresh. - Drink it fresh.
Tap. Hazy deep golden color with a thin white head. Aroma of mandarin, spices and grain. Medium sweet, bitter taste. Medium body.-- rated with beerbasher/winphone

Blonde dorée pale, mousse crémeuse. Nez fruité dagrumes, poire, pomme, bonbon. Bouche sur les agrumes, citron, litchi, caramel. Légèrement sucrée, belle amertume, un peu de corps, belle crabo. Très bonne bière.!

Tap@ølhuscph. Yellow light hazy. Green berries, citrus hoppy nose, light sort of bland maltyness. Well bitterred med bodied, quite dry feel. Tasty, refreshing citrus hoppy drink. Sort of onesided though..-- bb

(Keg at Ølhus København, 20141104) The beer poured golden and hazy. Its head was medium sized and white. Aroma had fruitiness, sweetness and malts. Palate was medium bodied and soft with medium carbonation. Flavours were fruitiness, citricness, malts and bitterness. Aftertaste was hoppy and bitter. A decent hoppy pale ale.

Tap@ olhus Kobenhavn. Unclear golden color, thick white head. Apricots, peachy aroma, gooseberries. Flavor has sweetness, gooseberries, dried Apricots. Some odd berry notes. Hoppy, dry finish. Cream ale ? OK.
Tap at Olhus Kopenhavn, Helsinki. Colour is cloudy golden with small white head. Aromas and flavors: Fruits, sweetness, hops, crispiness and malts. Cream ale?

Draught @ Ølhus København

Pours orange with a smooth head. Aroma of fruits, caramel, creamy toffee, malts and citrus. Taste is hoppy, caramely and smooth with some creamy toffee notes. Finish is smooth, hoppy and fruity. Interesting, quite hoppy for a cream ale. Feels more like a sweetish APA.

Draught. Slightly unclear golden in color with a whitish head. Notes of citrus fruits, summer meadow and grounded black pepper in aroma. Mmm, nice.
Light biting peppery spicyness in taste, bit of grapefruity bitterness and some grainy hints in taste at first. Towards the end also some lemony juicyness and fruity sweet notes appears. Somewhat bitter finish though. Crisp and refreshing for that matter.

Draught @ Ølhus København. Aroma is hoppy and grainy with tropical fruits. Feels heavy-ish. Flavour has lots of grapefruit, grainy malt, some peaches and hints of grass. Well hopped, well balanced. The grainy malt tones behind the hop wall are the only signs of lager here. Quite nice.

Colore dorato con un bel cappuccio bianco di schiuma. Al naso subito note di frutta esotica che lasciano spazio a frutta rossa e lieve buccia di agrumi. Corpo medio, morbido con note di pompelmo. Aroma di cereali con finale amaro.

Draught at Mikkeller & Friends.
Hazy amber coloured with a small white head.
Fruity aroma of hops and citrus peel with notes of exotic fruits and pine needles.
Fruity flavour of hops and citrus peel with notes of pine needles.
Hoppy finish.

33 cL bottle. Pours clear and golden orange with a huge white head. Aroma is citrusy and grassy. Smooth fruity, peachy, grassy and slight citrusy. Smooth fruity, grassy and light toasted malty. Bitter and smooth fruity finish.
Bottled. A golden beer with a lazing beige head. The aroma has notes of spices, malt, and caramel. The flavor is sweet with notes of straw, hops, flowers, and spices, leading to a bitter finish.
